bib_record.title: J-pi= 0+ states in the (fp) shell excited in the (3He,n) reaction

free_txt: Neutrons were detected in 10.2 cm diameter
NE213 liquid scintillators - of thickness 2.5 cm or
3.8 cm mounted on 12.7 cm photo-multipliers.The fourth
counter was used for timing stabilization. It
consisted of a 1 cm thick plastic scintillator
mounted on a 56 AVP Amperex photomultiplier, with
the scintillator about 0.5 m from the target.
The uncertainty in excitation is estimated
to be +-50keV for stronger transitions at low excitat.
For some of the weaker states or states at
high excitation with high background, the
uncertainty is estimated to be +-0.1 MeV.
